narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I have learned a great amount about writing and reading Spanish. Speaking was not as heavy an emphasis in this course, but I have the confidence to read whatever Spanish that was given to me.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: A strength of the course is that the workload is so heavy, it is hard to fall under the bridge. But a weakness of the course is that if one person does fall under the bridge then it is impossible to catch up without a tutor.
Rigorous learning and different exercises were very helpful. Excellent!

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: If you are looking for a hurdle-free gut language class, you're out of luck! L1 Spanish will keep you on your toes at least two hours a day, seven days a week. But if you are looking to pour your heart and soul into learning a language, Spanish L1 is for you!
Absolutely! It is so much fun.
